# TypeScript Naming Conventions

## Variables

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use camelCase | `recordCount` | `record_count`, `RecordCount` |
| Be descriptive | `userEmail` | `ue`, `x` |
| Avoid abbreviations | `configuration` | `cfg`, `config` (context-dependent) |
| Acronyms as words | `customerId` | `customerID` |

## Constants

| Context | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Local (function scope) | camelCase | `const maxRetries = 3` |
| Module-level exported | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `export const MAX_CONNECTIONS = 8` |
| Class static readonly | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `static readonly DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 3000` |

## Functions

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use camelCase | `sendEmail` | `SendEmail`, `send_email` |
| Start with verb | `getUserInfo` | `userInfo` |
| Handlers: `handle*` or `on*` | `handleClick` | `clickHandler` |

## Classes

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use PascalCase | `UserManager` | `userManager` |
| Use nouns | `PaymentService` | `ProcessPayment` |
| No `Class` suffix | `InternalHelper` | `InternalHelperClass` |

## Interfaces

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use PascalCase | `AccountInfo` | `accountInfo` |
| NO `I` prefix | `User` | `IUser` |
| NO `Interface` suffix | `Order` | `OrderInterface` |
| Properties in camelCase | `firstName` | `FirstName` |

## Type Aliases

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use PascalCase | `ComponentProps` | `componentProps` |
| NO `Type` suffix | `Address` | `AddressType` |
| Properties in camelCase | `ageInYears` | `age_in_years` |

## Enums

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Enum name: PascalCase | `StatusCode` | `statusCodes` |
| Members: PascalCase OR CONSTANT_CASE | `Ok` or `OK` | Mixed casing |
| Be consistent within project | Pick one style | `{ Ok, NOT_FOUND }` |

## Generics

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Single letter for simple | `T`, `K`, `V` | `type` |
| PascalCase if descriptive | `Item`, `Key` | `item`, `key` |
| Common: T=Type, K=Key, V=Value | `Map<K, V>` | `Map<key, value>` |

## Private Members

| Rule | Good | Bad |
|------|------|-----|
| Use `private` keyword | `private value` | `private _value` |
| NO underscore prefix | `count` | `_count` |
